 4. the person playing whist is somewhere between the person playing mah-jongg and the person playing chess##7
 5. the person playing chess is somewhere to the left of the person who likes red##5
 6. the person playing mah-jongg is not to the left of the person who likes lavender##8
 7. the person playing chess is not the person who likes red##6
 8. the person who likes red is somewhere to the right of the person who likes lavender##5
 9. the person who likes blue is not to the left of the person who likes lavender##8
10. the person playing chess is on the left or right of the person who likes blue##3
11. the person who likes ivory is on the left of the person who likes lavender##1
12. the person playing whist is somewhere to the left of the person playing go##5
13. the person who likes aquamarine is on the left of the person playing go##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1     |     2     |   3    |   4    |     5     |
